com.betfair.cougar.core.impl.ev

Class ContainerAwareExecutionVenue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.betfair.cougar.core.impl.ev.BaseExecutionVenue
      • com.betfair.cougar.core.impl.ev.ServiceRegisterableExecutionVenue
        • com.betfair.cougar.core.impl.ev.ContainerAwareExecutionVenue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CougarStartingGate, ExecutionVenue, ServiceRegistrar, ExportableRegistration, EventListener, org.springframework.context.ApplicationListener

    @ManagedResource
public class ContainerAwareExecutionVenue
extends ServiceRegisterableExecutionVenue
implements CougarStartingGate, ExportableRegistration
    Implementation of ExecutionVenue which is aware of the Spring container, and of the JMXControl. It will ensure that once the Spring application is loaded all registered Exportable beans will be registered with the JMXControl. This implementation is also a CougarStartingGate, and notifies any registered listeners of when Spring is loaded and the application is ready to start.

      • onApplicationEvent

        public void onApplicationEvent(org.springframework.context.ApplicationEvent event)
        In the case of ContextRefreshedEvent (that is, once all Spring configuration is loaded), the following actions will be taken:
      • the superclass's onAppEvent will initialise all services
      • The JMXControl will be retrieved from the application context and all registered Exportable implementations will be exported
      • All registered StartingGateListeners will be notified that the starting gate is open
      • A status check will be made on every registered service, with the status logged
